      <abstract>
        <p><italic>Streptococcus pneumoniae</italic> is not commonly considered an agent of urinary tract infections. We report 3 children with urinary tract abnormalities who had high numbers of <italic>S. pneumoniae</italic> in their urine (<underline>&gt;</underline>10<sup>4</sup> CFU/mL) and varying clinical symptoms.</p>
      </abstract>
